{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking paper","id":"r150907","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-QNCnQ0xOBwQ\/XZQxhN8kG0I\/AAAAAAAAcv0\/cGstzAzuBbcW2DF5wIE9c1tt_KdTGbqjgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_tcfy291zYWDpUdgq.png","title":"Meatloaf filled with Spinach and Cheese","publishedAt":"2017-06-01T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"20 g extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for greasing"},{"content":"50 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)"},{"content":"50 g onions, quartered"},{"content":"1 garlic clove, or to taste"},{"content":"4 sprigs fresh parsley, leaves only"},{"content":"40 g breadcrumbs"},{"content":"400 g beef mince, broken in pieces"},{"content":"2 medium eggs"},{"content":"½ tsp ground black pepper"},{"content":"2 tsp salt"},{"content":"50 g Gruyère cheese, sliced (2-3 mm)"},{"content":"25 g fresh baby spinach"},{"content":"½ - 1 garlic clove, to taste"},{"content":"450 g yellow peppers, cut in pieces (3-4 cm)"},{"content":"4 - 5 fresh basil leaves"},{"content":"400 g tinned chopped tomatoes"},{"content":"200 g water"},{"content":"1 pinch sugar              (optional)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"35 g","fat":"31 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"18 g","calories":"2128 kJ \/ 508 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Grease Varoma dish and set aside."},{"content":"Place Parmesan cheese, onions, 1 garlic clove and parsley in mixing bowl and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add breadcrumbs, beef mince, eggs, black pepper and 1 tsp salt and knead <b>1 min\/<b>. Transfer mixture to a sheet of baking paper (40 cm x 40 cm) and spread out to create a rectangular shape (approx. 25 cm x 20 cm, 1 cm thick). Arrange Gruyère cheese and baby spinach leaves evenly over the meat."},{"content":"Roll up meat with aid of baking paper to create a loaf shape. Remove baking paper and place meatloaf in greased Varoma dish."},{"content":"Place extra virgin olive oil, ½-1 garlic clove, peppers and basil in mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 5<b>, then sauté <b>3 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add chopped tomatoes, water, 1 tsp salt and sugar, set Varoma in position and cook <b>40 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Set Varoma aside and allow meatloaf to cool for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, insert measuring cup and blend sauce <b>40 sec\/speed 8<b>. Carefully remove meatloaf from Varoma, cut in slices and serve with sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<i>This is not your ordinary meatloaf. Carefully rolled around a Gruyère-spinach filling, gently steamed to preserve a tender and moist interior and served with a fruity tomato and yellow pepper sauce, it’s excellent both hot and cold. Great for a lunchbox or a picnic, or can also be served at a dinner party or family supper.<\/i>","Gruyère cheese can be replaced with other cheeses (e.g. smoked mozzarella, Gouda).<br>- For an easy side dish, in <b>step 6<b> steam up to <b>400 g vegetables<b> (e.g. carrots, potatoes, green beans, courgettes, broccoli), cut in bite-size pieces, in simmering basket. Remove simmering basket when the vegetables are cooked to your liking."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","1h 15m","4 portions"]}